<title>USA: Software Spectrum adopts rights plan.</title>
<headline>Software Spectrum adopts rights plan.</headline>
<dateline>GARLAND, Texas 1996-12-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Software Spectrum Inc said on Friday its board of directors adopted a shareholder rights plan to ensure they recieved fair treatment in case of a takeover attempt.</p>
<p>&quot;The company has taken strategic steps throughout the last year that will affect Software Spectrum's positioning for years to come,&quot; Judy Sims, chief executive officer, said.</p>
<p>The plan does not prevent a takeover but rather encouraged potential buyers to negotiate with the board, the company said. The rights plan also guarded against partial tender offers and other abusive tactics, it said.</p>
<p>-- New York newsdesk 212-859-1610</p>
